    • registerApiImplementor

      public void registerApiImplementor(ApiImplementor impl)
      Registers the given ApiImplementor to the ZAP API.

      The implementor is not registered if the API implementor prefix is already in use.

      Note: The preferred method to add an ApiImplementor is through the method ExtensionHook.addApiImplementor(ApiImplementor) when the corresponding extension is hooked. Only use this method if really necessary.

      Parameters:
      impl - the implementor that will be registered
      See Also:
      • removeApiImplementor(ApiImplementor)

    • removeApiImplementor

      public void removeApiImplementor(ApiImplementor impl)
      Removes the given ApiImplementor from the ZAP API.

      Since 2.8.0, the callbacks previously created for the implementor are removed as well.

      Parameters:
      impl - the implementor that will be removed
      Since:
      2.1.0
      See Also:

    • getBaseURL

      public String getBaseURL(API.Format format, String prefix, API.RequestType type, String name, boolean proxy)
      Returns a URI for the specified parameters.

      An one time nonce query parameter is added to the resulting URL, if required (that is, not a view). In this case the URL is ended with an ampersand (for example, https://zap/format/prefix/action/name/?apinonce=xyz&), otherwise it has a trailing slash (for example, http://zap/format/prefix/view/name/).

      Parameters:
      format - the format of the API response
      prefix - the prefix of the API implementor
      type - the request type
      name - the name of the endpoint
      proxy - if true then the URI returned will only work if proxying via ZAP, i.e. it will start with http://zap/..
      Returns:
      the URL to access the defined endpoint
      See Also:
      • getBaseURL(boolean)

    • getBaseURL

      public String getBaseURL(boolean proxy)
      Gets the base URL to access the ZAP API, possibly proxying through ZAP.

      If proxying through ZAP the base URL will use the custom domain, "zap".

      The resulting base URL has a trailing slash, for example, https://127.0.0.1/ or https://zap/.

      Parameters:
      proxy - true if the URL will be accessed while proxying through ZAP, false otherwise.
      Returns:
      the base URL to access the ZAP API.
      Since:
      2.7.0
